modules.description: This module enables low-level manipulation of binary data through mutable byte buffers backed by Cstruct bigarrays, offering operations to slice, shift, and directly read/write primitive values with precise endianness control. It supports in-place modifications and conversion between immutable Cstruct windows and mutable Mstruct buffers, facilitating efficient parsing and serialization of binary formats like network protocols or file headers. Utilities for delimiter-based parsing, memory-safe peeks, and temporary buffer setup/teardown address common use cases in systems programming and data format interoperability.
